5494188.title: Matlab not showing graphs
5494188.message: Dear class, If when publishing your Matlab to PDF it refuses to include a particular figure, try adding "snapnow" after the plot. This will force Matlab to include a picture of the most recently generated figure. Jamie Conway

5471220.title: Correction on the Last Example from Today's Class
5471220.message: Dear Students, I hope you are all doing well. I wanted to let you know that there was a minor mistake in the last example we discussed in today's class. I've made the necessary corrections and included an explanation on the last slide of the attached presentation. Additionally, I believe some of you might still have doubts about the limit of the solution as time approaches negative infinity. I've provided more details on this topic in the corrected slides, so please take a moment to review them carefully. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions or need further clarification. I appreciate your understanding! Best, S.

5464385.title: MATH246 Guided Study Sessions
5464385.message: Good Afternoon, My name is Logan Maroclo and I’ll be leading GSS for Conway’s sections this semester. Guided Study Sessions are group review sessions for traditionally difficult courses held twice a week for 50 minutes. Any section of the class is welcome to attend at any time during the semester. Currently, sessions will take place on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 5:00 - 6:00 PM in room MTH0101. Later in the semester I will share a google drive with material used in these sessions for anyone who is not able to make it. Sessions begin next week on Tuesday 9/3 and if you have any questions please feel free to contact me at lmaroclo@terpmail.umd.edu. Thanks, Logan Maroclo
